What is insertAdjacentHTML()?
insertAdjacentHTML() is a DOM method used to insert HTML code (string) directly into the 
page at a specific position relative to an element.

var_in_to_insert.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend',val_which_to_insert)
beforeend --> to insert at end
beforebegin --> to insert at first




What is appendChild()?
appendChild() adds a DOM element (node) as the last child of a parent.